  "content_id": "8823641a-919c-4880-9305-f481f5b5e58f",
  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers whose employees receive third-party awards or incentives",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<p>As an employer, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations if your employees receive third-party awards.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"whats-included\">What’s included</h2>\n\n<p>Third-party awards are normally incentives provided by someone other than you. For example, if you run a car dealership, your employee might receive an award from a car manufacturer.</p>\n\n<p>Awards can include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>cash</li>\n  <li>vouchers</li>\n  <li>cheques</li>\n  <li>other gifts</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "overview",
        "title": "Overview"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>What you have to report and pay depends on what kind of third-party award your employee receives, and whether you arrange the award.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"cash-and-cash-exchangeable-goods\">Cash and cash-exchangeable goods</h2>\n\n<p>The third party must deduct <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax from the award and pay it to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>You must deduct Class 1 National Insurance on the combined value of the award and the <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax paid on it by the third party.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"non-cash-goods\">Non-cash goods</h2>\n\n<h3 id=\"if-the-third-party-arranges-the-award\">If the third party arranges the award</h3>\n\n<p>They must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>account for the tax due on the award - this should be done by entering a Taxed Award Scheme (see the <a href=\"/expenses-and-benefits-third-party-awards/technical-guidance\">technical guidance</a> at the end of this guide)</li>\n  <li>pay any Class 1A National Insurance due on the value of the award and on the tax paid on it</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Warning\" class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>In some instances Class 1 National Insurance will be due instead, eg if your employee’s personal bills are paid on their behalf. In this case you will need to deduct and pay them.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3 id=\"if-you-arrange-the-award\">If you arrange the award</h3>\n\n<p>In this case:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the tax due on the award must still be paid by the third party</li>\n  <li>you must pay any Class 1A National Insurance that’s due</li>\n</ul>\n\n",
        "slug": "what-to-report-and-pay",
        "title": "What to report and pay"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>The value of the third-party award depends on what the award is.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"cash\">Cash</h2>\n\n<p>The value to use is the amount of cash awarded, including the <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax paid.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"vouchers\">Vouchers</h2>\n\n<p>If the award consists of vouchers, then the value to use is the cost to the third party of providing the vouchers, including the <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax paid.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"other-gifts\">Other gifts</h2>\n\n<p>If the award is something other than vouchers, use the cost to the third party of providing the award.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "work-out-the-value",
        "title": "Work out the value"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>The following guides contain more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim11200.htm\">incentive awards</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/nimmanual/nim16350.htm\">third-party benefits</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/EIM11235.htm\">incentive award schemes: taxed award scheme arrangements</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/nimmanual/nim02375.htm\">Class 1 National Insurance : Earnings of employees and office holders : taxed award schemes</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "technical-guidance",
        "title": "Technical guidance"
      }
    ]
  },
